    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The **attribute** is not set but the underlying **property** is actually set. You can inspect the selected element from the console. You'll be able to see that `node.selected` returns `true` for the selected option and `false` otherwise. Here is [an example](https://developer.mozilla.org/fr/docs/Web/HTML/Element/select) where you can give it a try. Note that HTML attribute and property are not the same. You can find more information about that on this [StackOverflow](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/6003819/what-is-the-difference-between-properties-and-attributes-in-html) post. \r\n\r\nDo you have a specific use case that requires the `selected` attribute to be present on the element?\r\n",
