    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "You can use the event emitted on `change` to retrieve the selected element. Here is an example with jQuery (see below). Is it what you want to achieve? If not please provide a bit more context or an example.\r\n\r\n```js\r\n$(\"select\").on(\"change\", function(event) {\r\n  const selectedValue = event.target.value;\r\n  // ...\r\n});\r\n```",
